reviews.review: Without going into spoilers 95% of the film was class, however I left the cinema feeling disgusted and angry for how Disney have treated Anakin and luke and made them useless. He is the chosen one and when you go see the film, you'll see why I'm upset. The film is good but it fell at the last hurdle.

This is a movie with exeptional sgi, unbeliveable acting, and a well done directing my J.J. Abrams. All in all, the skywalker saga concludes in a stunning and satisfying ending that will serve every fan who has ever loved the Star Wars saga!
Wtf? They brought Palpatine to be killed by Mary Sue? That's it? No plot, they rape old movies by their choices etc. Worst star wars movie ever.

Without getting into spoilers, for me this was a film that wrapped up the skywalker saga well, and, even though pretending that the last Jedi didn't exist pulled off an almost impossible task of ending one of the biggest franchises in cinema history, it's not a perfectly made film by any stretch of the imagination but it's produced well and even though jumpy and having a break neck pace, the film worked for me by the end with a good conclusion with lots of nostalgic moments, a must see for ANY Star Wars fans ( MINOR SPOILER more prequels links than I would've thought)
Loved it !! The sequel we always wanted
Addressed the mess Johnson created, still no real plot. Emperor died in Ep. 6, bringing him back is a re-run of Ep. 6.

If you see it as a movie goer, you will like it. Visuals are good and story is ok. Some characters are written well but no different from your average sci-fi flick

If you see it as a Star Wars fan, you will feel like someone set fire to all you have loved and shat on its ashes. It breaks lore and continuity it has established for years and is nothing but nostalgia baiting and retconning the movie. Frankly you'd get a better story from the Dark Empire books and I haven't even read them, but I believe they are more faithful than this.
Absolutely loved it. Satisfying ending to the sequel trilogy.

This was a huge disappointment. I've been waiting over 30 years for the completion of the story and it seemed so lazily written and chaotic. After seeing this movie, I want Men in Black to erase my memory so I can go back and enjoy the original trilogy with prequels.
Ends where we started, nicely paced. Several twists, great fun and a hit finish. Enjoyed every minute!
